Sheet1.PopUpContent: J Sainsbury plc, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the food, general merchandise and clothing retailing, and financial services activities in the United Kingdom. It operates through four segments: Retail – Food; Retail – General Merchandise & Clothing; Financial Services; and Property Investment. The company operates various store formats, including convenience stores and supermarkets, as well as offers organic produce under the Food to Go and FreeFrom names. It is also involved in an online grocery and general merchandise operations; and provides home, clothing, technology, leisure, toy, and electrical products, as well as groceries and loyalty programs, and energy solutions. As of March 11, 2017, the company operated 605 supermarkets and 809 convenience stores, as well as 59 Argos Digital stores, 11 Habitat stores, and 207 Digital Collection points. In addition, the company invests in and develops real estate properties; and offers financial services, such as loans portfolio comprising credit cards and storecards, personal loans, insurance, and travel money. J Sainsbury plc was founded in 1869 and is headquartered in London, the United Kingdom.

1) KFC Corporation, also known as Kentucky Fried Chicken, operates a chain of chicken restaurants in the United States and internationally. The company provides sandwiches, sides, desserts, drinks, sauces, fill ups, buttermilk biscuits, and other products; big box meals, popcorn nuggets, and kid’s meals; and chicken products, including chicken hot wings, chicken sandwiches, and fried chicken products. The company also franchises its restaurants. KFC Corporation was founded in 1952 and is based in Louisville, Kentucky. KFC Corporation operates as a subsidiary of KFC Holding Co.     

2) YUM! Brands, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, develops, operates, and franchises quick service restaurants worldwide. It operates in three segments: the KFC Division, the Pizza Hut Division, and the Taco Bell Division. The company operates restaurants under the KFC, Pizza Hut, and Taco Bell brands, which specialize in chicken, pizza, and Mexican-style food categories. As of December 31, 2017, it had 21,487 KFC units; 16,748 Pizza Hut units; and 6,849 Taco Bell units. The company was formerly known as TRICON Global Restaurants, Inc. and changed its name to YUM! Brands, Inc. in May 2002. YUM! Brands, Inc. was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Louisville, Kentucky.

Starbucks Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a roaster, marketer, and retailer of specialty coffee worldwide. The company operates in four segments: Americas; China/Asia Pacific; Europe, Middle East, and Africa; and Channel Development. Its stores offer coffee and tea beverages, roasted whole bean and ground coffees, single-serve and ready-to-drink coffee and tea products, and food and snacks; and various food products, such as pastries, breakfast sandwiches, and lunch items. The company also licenses its trademarks through licensed stores, and grocery and foodservice accounts. It offers its products under the Starbucks, Teavana, Tazo, Seattle’s Best Coffee, Evolution Fresh, La Boulange, Ethos, Frappuccino, Starbucks Doubleshot, Starbucks Refreshers, premium Tazo, and Starbucks VIA brand names. As of November 2, 2017, the company operated 27,339 stores across 75 countries. Starbucks Corporation was founded in 1971 and is based in Seattle, Washington.

1) Poundland Limited operates as discount and value retailers. The company owns and operates single price discount stores. It offers sweets and snacks, grocery, canned food, soft drinks, hair care and skincare products, toiletries, household accessories, clothing, and stationary and craft products. The company was founded in 1990 and is based in Willenhall, United Kingdom. Poundland Limited operates as a subsidiary of Poundland Group plc.    

2) Steinhoff Europe AG, through its subsidiaries, retails, sources, and manufactures furniture, household goods, and general merchandise in Europe and Australia. The company was founded in 1964 and is based in Brunn am Gebirge, Austria. Steinhoff Europe AG operates as a subsidiary of Steinhoff Möbel Holding GmbH.

1) Timpson Limited, a retail service company, provides key cutting, shoe repair, engraving, and watch repair services in the United Kingdom and Ireland. It also offers photo processing, photo ID and passport photo processing, dry cleaning and laundry, carpet cleaning machine hire, mobile phone repairs, and locksmith services, as well as remote and non-remote car keys, photo gifts, and key and locker solutions. In addition, the company sells signs, business products, engraved products, books, gifts, watch straps, locksmith and security products, keys and lockers, and lighters. It sells products and services through a network of its stores and franchises, as well as online. Timpson Limited was formerly known as Shoe Care Centres Limited and changed its name to Timpson Limited in November 2004. The company was founded in 1865 and is based in Manchester, United Kingdom. Timpson Limited operates as a subsidiary of Timpson Group Plc. 

2) Timpson Group PLC operates as a shoe repairer, key cutter, engraver and watch repairer in the United Kingdom. The company was founded in 1865 and is based in Manchester, United Kingdom. The company operates as a subsidiary of Offerhappy Ltd.

200 Degrees Holdings Ltd operates a chain of coffee shops. It wholesales coffee beans and machines including espresso machines, drip filter machines, and pour-over kits to cafes, delis, bars, and restaurants. The company also operates Barista Schools which offer courses for home brewing methods, how to operate a professional espresso machine, and latte art. The company was founded in 2012 and is based in Nottingham, United Kingdom.

Patisserie Holdings plc, together with its subsidiaries, operates in the casual dining sector in the United Kingdom. The company’s stores formats include cafés, concessions, brasseries, takeaways, kiosks, and an online channel. Its stores offer cakes, pastries, snacks, meals, and hot and cold drinks. The company operates 134 stores under the Patisserie Valerie brand, 21 stores under the Druckers – Vienna Patisserie brand, 23 stores under Philpotts brand, 5 stores under Baker & Spice brand, and 1 bakery under the Flour Power City Bakery brand. Patisserie Holdings plc was founded in 1926 and is based in Birmingham, the United Kingdom.

Office Holdings LTD. owns and operates a chain of retail stores that sell footwear and accessories for men, women, and kids in the United Kingdom and internationally. Its stores sell shoes, heels, boots, and trainers; accessories, such as backpacks, handbags and purses, shoe care products and laces, caps and hats, and socks; and women's and men's clothing. The company also sells products online. Office Holdings LTD. was founded in 1981 and is based in London, United Kingdom. It has store locations in the East Midlands, east of England, Greater London, Ireland, northeast, northwest, Scotland, south, southeast, southwest, the West Midlands, Wales, and Yorkshire and the Humber regions of the United Kingdom, as well as in New York, New York; Chicago, Illinois; Las Vegas, Nevada; and Oberhausen, Dusseldorf, Bonn, Hamburg, Cologne, and Wiesbaden, Germany. As of December 4, 2015, Office Holdings LTD. operates as a subsidiary of Shoo 615 Ltd.


Truworths Limited owns and operates a chain of retail stores that sell fashion merchandise for men, women, and kids in South Africa and the rest of Africa. The company offers tops, bottoms, knitwear, skirts and dresses, sweats, jackets and coats, shoes and bags, formalwear, maternity products, accessories, and fragrances for women; tops, bottoms, sweats, jackets and coats, shoes, formalwear, and accessories for men; and beauty products. It also sells its products online. The company was founded in 1917 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa. Truworths Limited operates as a subsidiary of Truworths International Ltd.

Sheet1.PopUpContent: Dixons Carphone plc operates as an electrical and telecommunications retailer and service company. The company operates through four segments: UK & Ireland, Nordics, Southern Europe, and Connected World Services (CWS). It offers various products and services in the United Kingdom and Ireland, including mobile handsets and other connected devices under the Carphone Warehouse brand; electrical and telecommunications products under the CurrysPCWorld Carphone Warehouse brand; computing products and services to business to business customers under the PC World Business name; travelling services with stores at airports under the Dixons Travel brand; and services under the Knowhow brand, as well a

Fusion Students Limited operates and manages student accommodation residences in Bristol, Newcastle, Cardiff, and Nottingham, United Kingdom. Its residences offer a range of amenities, which include double beds, flat-screen TVs, kitchens, storage space, club lounges, study facilities, private gyms, gaming rooms, private cinemas, residents’ bars, broadband and Wi-Fi facilities, and laundry and social services. The company was incorporated in 2014 and is based in Bristol, United Kingdom.
n/a

The Second Cup Ltd. operates as a specialty coffee retailer in Canada. It offers coffee-based products and other beverages, as well as various complementary products, including pastries, sandwiches, muffins, cookies, coffee accessories, and coffee-related gift items. As of March 8, 2017, the company had operated approximately 290 franchised and company owned cafes under the Second Cup Coffee Co. name. The Second Cup Ltd. was founded in 1975 and is headquartered in Mississauga, Canada.

EE Limited provides mobile and fixed communication services in the United Kingdom. It offers mobile, TV, and broadband services. The company provides its services to retail and business customers under the EE, Orange, and T-Mobile brands. EE Limited provides services to approximately 31 million connections across its mobile, fixed, and wholesale networks. It also sells handsets and related accessories; and provides management support, pension trustee, and finance services. The company was formerly known as Everything Everywhere Limited and changed its name to EE Limited in September 2013. The company was founded in 2010 and is based in Hatfield, the United Kingdom. EE Limited is a subsidiary of BT Group plc.

BT Group plc provides communications services worldwide. Its Consumer segment sells telephones, baby monitors, and Wi-Fi extenders through high street retailers and the online BT Shop, as well as through Website BT.com; and offers home phone, copper and fiber broadband, TV, and mobile services in various packages. The company’s EE segment offers 2G, 3G, and 4G mobile network services; and broadband, fixed-voice, and TV services, as well as postpaid and prepaid plans, and emergency services network. It also sells 4G mobile phones, tablets, connected devices, and mobile broadband devices from various manufacturers. Its Business and Public Sector segment provides fixed voice, mobility, fiber an

E-Cigarette Direct LLC supplies and sells electronic cigarettes online. It provides electronic cigarette kits, electronic cigarette cartridges, chargers and batteries, and electronic liquids. The company was founded in 2008 and is based in Swansea, United Kingdom.

Ollie Quinn Limited designs and retails eyewear for men and women. The company offers optical eyewear and sunglasses; and in-store opticians and eye exams. It serves customers through its stores in London, Leeds, and Bristol, United Kingdom. The company was formerly known as Bailey Nelson LDN Limited and changed its name to Ollie Quinn Limited in January 2017. Ollie Quinn Limited was founded in 2013 and is based in London, United Kingdom. It also has operations in Canada and the United States.

Whitbread Group Plc owns and operates hotels, restaurants and coffee shops. The company was incorporated in 1889 and is based in Dunstable, United Kingdom. Whitbread Group Plc operates as a subsidiary of Whitbread PLC.

WH Smith PLC operates as a retailer in the United Kingdom and internationally. It operates through two segments, High Street and Travel. The High Street segment sells stationery products, including greetings cards, general stationery, art and craft, and gifting products; news and impulse products, such as newspapers, magazines, confectionery, and drinks; and books. As of August 31, 2017, it operated 611 stores. This segment also offers its stationery, books, magazines, and gifts through whsmith.co.uk; and its online personalized greetings cards through funkypigeon.com and funkypigeon.ie. The Travel segment offers convenience, books, and news for travelling customers. As of August 31, 2017, i.

LetterOne Holdings S.A. is a private equity and venture capital firm specializing in startups, industry consolidation, distressed, and turnaround investments. The firm invests currently through strategic equity holdings in listed companies, or through the ownership of private companies. It prefers to invest in following sectors: oil and gas, technology, and telecommunications. The firm seeks to invest in energy and hydrocarbon projects with a focus on exploration and production, oilfield services, oil and gas projects, upstream projects, conventional and unconventional reserves, and other energy projects. The firm invests globally with a focus on Russia, United States, and Europe. It also

Arcadia Group Limited owns, operates, and franchises a chain of fashion stores and outlets in the United Kingdom and internationally. It offers its products under brands, such as Burton, Dorothy Perkins, Evans, Miss Selfridge, Topshop, Topman, Wallis, and Outfit. The company operates through retail stores and online. The company was founded in 1903 and is based in London, United Kingdom with additional offices in London and Leeds, United Kingdom.

Industria de Diseño Textil, S.A. engages in the retail and on-line distribution of clothing, footwear, accessories and household textile products through various store formats in Spain, rest of Europe, the Americas, Asia, and internationally. The company’s store formats include Zara, Pull & Bear, Massimo Dutti, Bershka, Stradivarius, Oysho, Zara Home, and Uterqüe. It operates 7,292 stores in 93 markets; and online stores in 41 markets. The company also engages in the textile manufacturing, design, real estate, and logistic activities; and provision of financial services. Industria de Diseño Textil, S.A. was founded in 1963 and is based in Arteixo, Spain.

River Island Clothing Co. Limited operates and franchises a chain of apparel stores. It offers clothing, dresses, tops, T-shirts/vests/sweats, coats/jackets, leather/leather look jackets, capes/kimonos, blazers, knitwear, jeans, skirts, trousers, shorts, leggings, coordinates/matching sets, playsuits/jumpsuits, swimwear/beachwear, and lingerie/nightwear; and shoes/boots, bags/purses, accessories, jewelers, watches, sunglasses, gifts, beauty products, and socks for women and girls. The company also provides clothing, T-shirts/vests, blazers, coats/jackets, chinos, hoodies/sweatshirts, jeans, joggers, jumpers/cardigans, polo shirts, pyjamas/onesies, shirts, shorts, suits, swim shorts, tops, trousers, underwear/socks, and waistcoats; and accessories, bags, gifts, jewelers, shoes/boots, sunglasses, and watches for men and boys. In addition, it designs and manufactures apparels. River Island Clothing Co. Limited was formerly known as Chelsea Girl Limited and changed its name to River Island Clothing Co. Limited in 1988. The company was founded in 1948 and is based in London, United Kingdom. It has stores in the United Kingdom, Ireland, Asia, the Middle East, Europe, and internationally. River Island Clothing Co. Limited operates as a subsidiary of River Island Holdings Limited.

Lush Retail Limited manufactures and sells handmade cosmetics and fragrances. It offers bath, body, face, shower, hair, makeup, shaving, and spa products; and perfumes and gifts. The company sells its products through its shops and spas in the United Kingdom. It also sells its products online to customers in the United Kingdom, Channel Islands, and internationally. The company was founded in 1995 and is based in Poole, United Kingdom. Lush Retail Limited operates as a subsidiary of Lush Ltd.

Wilko Retail Ltd. sells garden products, outdoor living products, home products, kitchen products, decorating products, DIY products, housewares, storage products, pets products, stationery, health and beauty products, and toys online. It offers sheds and summerhouses, greenhouses and accessories; and fencing and screening products, tools and equipment, seeds and bulbs, fertilizers and weedkillers, watering and pond products, maintenance and security products, and wild bird and wildlife products. The company provides garden furniture, summerhouses and log cabins, chimneys and firepits, garden décor products, garden lights, outdoor leisure products, and dinnerware; and bathroom, bedding, window dressing, soft furnishings, home décor, home accessories, lighting, kids zone, rugs and doormats, haberdashery, and furniture. It offers dinnerware, dining, cooking, baking and preserving, kitchen appliances, homebrew, utensils and gadgets, food storage, food preparation, textiles and tableware, dining room furniture, and kitchen furniture. Wilko Retail Ltd. delivers products to Mainland England, Wales, and parts of Scotland, as well as to Isle of Wight, Isle of Man, Isle of Scilly, Scottish Highlands, Grampians, and Northern Ireland. The company was founded in 1930 and is based in Worksop, United Kingdom. Wilko Retail Ltd. operates as a subsidiary of Wilkinson Hardware Stores Ltd.

JD Sports Fashion Plc engages in the retail of branded sports fashionwear, and outdoor clothing and equipment. It operates through Sports Fashion and Outdoor segments. The company retails sports and fashion clothing, footwear, and sports and leisure goods, as well as distributes sports clothing and accessories, footwear and apparel, and rugby clothing and accessories. It offers products under the JD, Size?, Chausport, Sprinter, Kooga, Kukri, Focus, Source Lab, Scotts, Tessuti, Cloggs, Nicholas Deakins, Footpatrol, Aktiesport, Mainline, Perry, JD Gyms, Blacks, Millets, Tiso, GO Outdoors, and Ultimate Outdoors brands. The company also operates online and catalog business under the getthelabel.com name. In addition, it licenses fashion brands and operates fitness centers. The company operates approximately 1300 stores. It has operations in the United Kingdom, the Republic of Ireland, France, Spain, Germany, the Netherlands, Italy, Portugal, Sweden, Denmark, Belgium, Malaysia, Australia, New Zealand, Canada, Dubai, Singapore, and Hong Kong. The company was founded in 1981 and is headquartered in Bury, the United Kingdom. JD Sports Fashion Plc is a subsidiary of Pentland Group Plc.

Ann Summers Ltd. operates lingerie products retail stores. It also offers sex toys, rampant rabbits, erotic products, bondage products, fancy dresses, nightwear, sex essentials, and gifts. It offers products for women. The company also sells products online. The company was founded in 1970 and is based in Whyteleafe, United Kingdom. It has stores in the United Kingdom, Ireland, and Spain. Ann Summers Ltd. operates as a subsidiary of Gold Group International Ltd.

Nationwide Building Society, together with its subsidiaries, provides retail financial services in the United Kingdom, the Isle of Man, and the Republic of Ireland. The company operates through Retail and Commercial segments. It offers current and savings, and ISA accounts; and residential mortgage, commercial real estate, project finance, social housing, personal and car loans, and home improvement loans, as well as loans to housing associations. The company also provides protection and investment products, financial planning services, credit cards, current account overdrafts, and treasury, liquidity, and discretionary services, as well as car, home, life and critical illness, income protection, travel, and mobile phone insurance products. In addition, it offers buy to let lending and deposit taking services. The company offers its products and services primarily through its branches, mobile, Internet, and telephone banking. Nationwide Building Society was founded in 1846 and is headquartered in Swindon, the United Kingdom.

Matalan Retail Limited operates as a clothing and homeware retailer in the United Kingdom. It offers clothing, shoes and accessories, and nightwear for women; clothing, shoes and accessories, and suits and formalwear for men; lingerie; and clothing, shoes and accessories, and school uniforms for boys and girls. The company also offers bedroom, bathroom, kitchen, dining room, living room, and garden and outdoor homewares; travel products and suitcases; and kids and nursery products. It sells products through retail and online stores. Matalan Retail Limited was formerly known as Matalan Discount Club (Cash & Carry) Ltd. and changed its name to Matalan Retail Limited in March 1998. The company was founded in 1985 and is based in Liverpool, United Kingdom with stores throughout the United Kingdom. Matalan Retail Limited operates as a subsidiary of Matalan Limited.

Missouri Topco Limited – ultimate owner of Matalan? Missouri Topco Limited sells clothing and homewares in the United Kingdom. The company sells its products through out-of-town retail outlets, primarily through the Matalan fascia. It operates 227 stores in the United Kingdom, which include 5 clearance stores. The company also sells its products online. In addition, it is involved in property, as well as distribution businesses; and provision of travel services. Missouri Topco Limited is based in Liverpool, the United Kingdom.

HMV Group plc engages in retailing pre-recorded music, video, electronic games, and related entertainment products under the HMV and Fopp brands. It offers multi-channel access to a selection of music, film and games, and other culture across various genres and formats, including live music and events through its hmvtickets platform, and ownership of MAMA venues and festivals. As of March 29, 2013, the company operated 219 stores; an online shop, www.hmv.com; and hmvdigital and hmvon-demand digital sites. It has operations in the United Kingdom, Ireland, Hong Kong, and Singapore. The company was founded in 1921 and is based in Marlow, United Kingdom. As of January 15, 2013, HMV Group plc is in liquidation.

Hilco Trading, LLC, doing business as Hilco Global, operates as an independent and diversified financial services company around the world. It offers asset valuation, asset monetization, and advisory services. The company serves as advisor, auctioneer, broker, agent, investor, and/or liquidator in various classes of tangible and intangible assets on a corporation’s balance sheet, including inventory, machinery and equipment, real estate, accounts receivable, IP addresses, trademarks, and intellectual property. It serves retailers, wholesalers, distributors and manufacturers, directly and through their lenders, and investors and advisors, including private equity firms, hedge funds, investment banks, law firms, turnaround professionals, accounting professionals, bankruptcy trustees, and receivers; and aerospace and defense, chemical processing, construction, technology, automotive, plastics, rolling stock, metals, power generation, industrial, metalworking, vehicle, IT, real estate, healthcare, and office industries primarily in North America, Central and South America, Europe, Asia, and Australia. The company was founded in 1987 and is based in Northbrook, Illinois with additional offices worldwide.

Thomas Cook Group plc provides leisure travel services in the United Kingdom, Continental Europe, Northern Europe, and Germany. The company operates through Group Tour Operator and Group Airline segments. It owns, manages, or franchises 190 own-brand hotels in 16 countries under the Casa Cook, Sunwing, Sunprime, Sunconnect, Sentido, Smartline, and Aldiana brands, as well as partner hotels. The company also operates an airline fleet of 93 aircrafts; and Academy of Excellence, which offers professional training and consulting packages, including mystery checks and quality audits, online reputation services, quality initiative, and individual training, and coaching and consulting packages for partner hotels. In addition, it provides ancillary products, including extra luggage, seat reservations, in-resort transfers, and room upgrades; tour operations and associated services; and scheduled and charter, and related services. The company offers its products through its Website and retail stores, as well as third party retail channels. Thomas Cook Group plc was founded in 1841 and is based in London, the United Kingdom.

Principality Building Society provides mortgage advances to members secured on residential property in the United Kingdom. The company also offers commercial mortgage loans. As of December 31, 2016, it had a network of 53 branches and 18 agency offices. The company was founded in 1860 and is based in Cardiff, the United Kingdom.

Dave Whelan Sports Limited, trading as DW Sports Fitness, retails sporting goods. It sells running, football, fitness, and rugby footwear; T-shirts, shorts, pants, hoodies, jackets, vests, tights, tops, track suits, and tees; socks, gloves, insoles, and hats; and base layers for men. The company also sells running and fitness footwear; T-shirts, tights, sports bras, pants, tanks, shorts, hoodies, jackets, vests, and tops; socks, bags, gloves, insoles, and hats; and base layers for women. In addition, it offers football, running, and rugby footwear; pants, shorts, T-shirts, tights, track suits, and hoodies; socks and bags; and base layers for juniors. Further, the company sells products online. It serves health club and retail business in the United Kingdom Northern Ireland. The company was founded in 2009 and is based in Wigan, United Kingdom. Dave Whelan Sports Limited is a former subsidiary of JJB Sports plc.

Superdrug Stores plc, a beauty and health retailing company, owns and operates a network of stores in England, Scotland, Wales, Northern Ireland, and the Republic of Ireland. Its stores sell makeup, skincare, fragrance, health and wellbeing, mother and baby care, hair care, and men’s care products, as well as toiletries and electricals. The company also offers beauty and toiletry products under its own brand; and online health services in the areas of men’s health, women’s health, sexual health, heart and lungs, travel health, and others. In addition, its some of the stores include in-store pharmacies with pharmacy consulting rooms, as well as nurse clinics that provide health checks. Further, the company sells products online. Superdrug Stores plc was formerly known as Leading Supermarkets Limited. The company was founded in 1964 and is based in Croydon, United Kingdom. As of July 20, 2001, Superdrug Stores plc operates as a subsidiary of Hutchison Whampoa Limited.

Arcadia Group Limited owns, operates, and franchises a chain of fashion stores and outlets in the United Kingdom and internationally. It offers its products under brands, such as Burton, Dorothy Perkins, Evans, Miss Selfridge, Topshop, Topman, Wallis, and Outfit. The company operates through retail stores and online. The company was founded in 1903 and is based in London, United Kingdom with additional offices in London and Leeds, United Kingdom.

Regatta Ltd. manufactures outdoor clothing and footwear for men, women, boys, and girls. The company offers jackets, fleece and hoodies, softshells, bodywarmers and gilets, T-shirts and tops, legwear, and accessories; trail shoes, walking boots, winter boots, wellies, socks, and footwear accessories; and rucksacks. It provides its products through retail stores in the United Kingdom and internationally. The company was incorporated in 1972 and is based in Manchester, United Kingdom. Regatta Ltd. operates as a subsidiary of Risol Imports Ltd.

Steinhoff Europe AG, through its subsidiaries, retails, sources, and manufactures furniture, household goods, and general merchandise in Europe and Australia. The company was founded in 1964 and is based in Brunn am Gebirge, Austria. Steinhoff Europe AG operates as a subsidiary of Steinhoff Möbel Holding GmbH.

Banco Santander, S.A., together with its subsidiaries, provides various retail and commercial banking products and services for individual and corporate clients worldwide. It offers demand and time deposits, and current and savings accounts; certificates of deposit; mortgages, auto finance, and personal loans; working capital finance; and debit and credit cards, as well as life and non-life insurance products. The company also provides cash management, trade finance, custody and securities, and securitization services; corporate loans; capital market products; and syndicated corporate finance services. In addition, it is involved in the corporate banking, treasury, and investment banking activities; fixed income and equity derivatives; trading and hedging derivatives; and brokerage of equities. Further, the company offers asset management, private banking, and processing services, as well as mobile and online banking services. It operates through a network of 13,697 branches. The company was formerly known as Banco Santander Central Hispano S.A. and changed its name to Banco Santander, S.A. in June 2007. Banco Santander, S.A. was founded in 1856 and is headquartered in Madrid, Spain.

YUM! Brands, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, develops, operates, and franchises quick service restaurants worldwide. It operates in three segments: the KFC Division, the Pizza Hut Division, and the Taco Bell Division. The company operates restaurants under the KFC, Pizza Hut, and Taco Bell brands, which specialize in chicken, pizza, and Mexican-style food categories. As of December 31, 2017, it had 21,487 KFC units; 16,748 Pizza Hut units; and 6,849 Taco Bell units. The company was formerly known as TRICON Global Restaurants, Inc. and changed its name to YUM! Brands, Inc. in May 2002. YUM! Brands, Inc. was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Louisville, Kentucky.

Company Overview
Lloyds Bank plc provides a range of banking and financial products and services in the United Kingdom and internationally. It operates through four segments: Retail, Commercial Banking, Consumer Finance, and Insurance. The Retail segment offers a range of financial service products, including current accounts, savings, and mortgages to wealth and small business customers. This segment also distributes insurance products, and a range of long-term savings and investment products. The Commercial Banking segment provides products, such as lending, transaction banking, working capital management, risk management, and debt capital markets services, as well as access to private equity. This segment serves SME, mid markets, global corporates, and financial institution clients. The Consumer Finance segment offers consumer lending products comprising motor finance, credit cards, and unsecured personal loans. The Insurance segment provides protection, pension, and investment products. The company was formerly known as Lloyds TSB Bank plc. Lloyds Bank plc was founded in 1765 and is based in London, the United Kingdom. Lloyds Bank plc is a subsidiary of Lloyds Banking Group plc.

SPAR International B.V. owns and operates food stores that include supermarkets and hypermarkets in Africa, the Asia Pacific and Middle East, and Western, Eastern, and Central Europe. The company offers bakery, breakfast, canned, dairy, drinks, frozen, healthy, indulgence, internationals, non food, pet care, value range, and condiments and cooking products. It has strategic partnerships with SPAR UAE and PT. Ramayana Lestari Sentosa Tbk. The company was founded in 1953 and is based in Amsterdam, the Netherlands.

TUI AG, together with its subsidiaries, provides tourism services worldwide. The company operates through Northern Region, Central Region, Western Region, Hotels and Resorts, Cruises, and Other Tourism segments. It is involved in the tour operation and airlines businesses, as well as owns and operates hotels and resorts. The company also operates cruise liners; and provides incoming agency services. It operates a fleet of 1,600 travel agencies, 150 aircrafts, and 16 cruise liners, as well as approximately 300 hotels with 214,000 beds. TUI AG is based in Hanover, Germany.

McDonald's Corporation operates and franchises McDonald's restaurants in the United States, Europe, the Asia/Pacific, the Middle East, Africa, Canada, Latin America, and internationally. The company's restaurants offer various food products, soft drinks, coffee, and other beverages. As of December 31, 2016, it operated 36,899 restaurants, including 31,230 franchised restaurants comprising 21,559 franchised to conventional franchisees, 6,300 licensed to developmental licensees, and 3,371 licensed to foreign affiliates; and 5,669 company-operated restaurants. McDonald's Corporation was founded in 1940 and is based in Oak Brook, Illinois.

The Works Stores Ltd. engages in the retail of books, art and craft products, stationery, toys and games, home and leisure products, office supplies, gifts, and kid’s products through its stores; and online. The company was formerly known as Remainders Limited and changed its name to The Works Stores Ltd. in January 2003. The Works Stores Ltd. was founded in 1981 and is based in Sutton Coldfield, United Kingdom with store locations in the United Kingdom and Ireland.

Trailfinders Ltd. provides travel agency services. The company offers Visa and passport, travel insurance, travel clinic, travel essentials, foreign exchange, airport parking and hotels, and airport lounge services. It also provides booking services related to flights, hotels, cruises, fly drives, rail journeys, tours, and car and motorhome hire. The company offers services to clients in Africa, Antarctic, Arctic, Australia, Canada, Alaska, the Caribbean, China, Hong Kong, Japan, Europe, India, Sri Lanka, Maldives, Mauritius, Seychelles, New Zealand, the Pacific, the Russian Federation, Central Asia, the United States, Canada, South and Central America, the South East Asia, the Middle East,

Toys “R” Us, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, operates as a retailer of toys and baby products. It operates through two segments, Domestic and International. The company offers products for newborns and children up to four years of age, including baby gear, infant care products, apparels, furniture, and room décors; boys and girls toys, such as action figures, dolls and doll accessories, and vehicles; and video game software, systems and accessories, tablets, portable electronics, and other related products. It also provides educational electronics and developmental toys consisting of Imaginaries products in the United States and World of Imagination products internationally; and con

FEXCO Holdings Ltd. provides finance and business services and solutions to customers worldwide. The company offers merchant solutions include Dynamic Currency Conversion, a point-of-purchase service that allows international Visa and MasterCard card users choose to pay in their own currency; Multi-Currency Pricing that allows merchants to price goods and services in various foreign currencies; Currency Assist, a treasury service that enables acquirers to offer merchants risk free processing and settlement options; FEXCO Switch, a payments switching solution for acquirers, merchants, and payment processors; E-Vouchers, an outsourced solution for ecommerce business; and tax free shopping serv

New Look Group Limited, through its subsidiaries, operates as a multichannel retail brand in the United Kingdom and internationally.
